Good baseline config

OpenCode supports project-level config with opencode.json at the repo root, and project config has highest precedence. It also supports JSONC and a schema URL.

A practical starting point:

{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "autoupdate": true,
  "server": {
    "port": 4096
  },
  "permission": {
    "bash": "ask",
    "edit": "ask",
    "webfetch": "allow"
  }
}

The permissions pattern above matches the official tools/config docs.

